reviewText: This certainly isn't a "great" sci-fi movie but for it's time it was pretty good.  I remembered it from years ago and had been looking for it originally on VHS then on DVD and finally found it and bought it.  It's a fun watch!
Title: Moon Zero Two

reviewText: Absolutely love this version, great picture quality too.  I've waited more than 25 years to see this movie again since I first saw it on TV and I was not disappointed !  I have the MOON ZERO TWO theme song (sung by Julie Driscoll) in my head since the first time I heard it and i absolutely love it!  Great entertainment and fun movie.
Title: Moon Zero Two

reviewText: BRITISH.BEST EVER moon movie i have EVER SEEN.When we colonize the moon we will need to see this film first.
Title: Moon Zero Two

reviewText: Where are Christopher Lee and Peter Cushing when you really need them? Hammer Films' big-budget foray into the "space cowboy" genre never takes off. Strictly drive-in fodder, "Moon Zero Two" (1969) opens with a dreadful animated credit sequence and maintains its cheesy weirdness. If you can survive the 100-minute running time, you will find some unintentional laughs.
Title: Moon Zero Two

reviewText: Been looking for a long time to get a copy of this much under rated sci-fi movie.  When it was new and I ran it for the first time as a projectionist in a theater, I thought it was going to be a silly cartoon.  Ended up being a good drama with a few "silly" parts.  I would tell anyone to buy if looking for this movie.
summary: Good DVD of an under rated movie
Title: Moon Zero Two
